                                                                                int factor)
        Computes a map of identified Uniform Fuzzy Hashes from a map of identified byte arrays of data and a factor.
        Type Parameters:
        T - Identifiers type.
        Parameters:
        byteArrays - Map of identified byte arrays of data.
        factor - Relation between data length and the hash mean number of blocks for each byte array of data. Must be greater than 2 and must be odd.
        Returns:
        Map of identified Uniform Fuzzy Hashes.

      • computeHashesFromFiles

        public static java.util.Map<java.lang.String,UniformFuzzyHash> computeHashesFromFiles(java.util.Collection<java.io.File> files,
                                                                                      int factor,
                                                                                      boolean nested)
                                                                               throws java.io.IOException
        Computes a map of identified Uniform Fuzzy Hashes from a collection of files of data (identifying them by their names) and a factor. Files which do not exist are ignored.
        Parameters:
        files - Collection of files of data.
        factor - Relation between data length and the hash mean number of blocks for each file of data. Must be greater than 2 and must be odd.
        nested - True to read files inside directories recursively. False to ignore directories.
        Returns:
        Map of identified Uniform Fuzzy Hashes.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - If an IOException occurs reading any of the files of data.

      • printHashToHashesSimilaritiesTable

        public static <T> void printHashToHashesSimilaritiesTable(java.util.Map<T,java.util.Map<UniformFuzzyHash.SimilarityTypes,java.lang.Double>> similarities,
                                                          int rowsLimit,
                                                          int truncateIdentifiers,
                                                          double markAbove,
                                                          double markBelow)
        Prints a table showing all the types of similarity between a Uniform Fuzzy Hash and a map of identified Uniform Fuzzy Hashes.
        Type Parameters:
        T - Identifiers type.
        Parameters:
        similarities - Map of identified similarities (As it is returned from the method computeHashToHashesSimilarities).
        rowsLimit - Introduce a number larger than 0 to limit the number of rows.
        truncateIdentifiers - Introduce a number larger than 0 to truncate the identifiers to a maximum length.
        markAbove - Mark all similarities above or equal to this threshold with a color. Introduce a negative number to not mark any similarity.
        markBelow - Mark all similarities below this threshold with a color. Introduce a negative number to not mark any similarity.
